## 2️⃣ Categorical Encoding

```python
# LABEL ENCODING (when ORDER exists):
membership_map = {'Free': 0, 'Silver': 1, 'Gold': 2}
df['membership_encoded'] = df['membership'].map(membership_map)

# ONE-HOT ENCODING (when NO order):
df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['city', 'device', 'category'],
                    drop_first=True,   # Avoid dummy variable trap!
                    dtype=int)         # True/False → 1/0
```

### Decision Rule:
```
Has Order?  → Label Encoding  (Free<Silver<Gold)
No Order?   → One-Hot Encoding (Mumbai, Delhi, Chennai)
> 50 cats?  → Target Encoding (advanced)
```

---

## 3️⃣ Feature Scaling

```python
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, MinMaxScaler

# StandardScaler: mean=0, std=1 (good for outliers)
scaler = StandardScaler()
df[cols] = scaler.fit_transform(df[cols])

# MinMaxScaler: 0 to 1 (good for Neural Networks)
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
df[cols] = scaler.fit_transform(df[cols])
```

### When to Scale:
| Algorithm | Scaling Needed? |
|-----------|----------------|
| Linear/Logistic Regression | ✅ Yes |
| SVM | ✅ Yes |
| Neural Networks | ✅ Yes (MinMax) |
| KNN | ✅ Yes |
| Decision Tree | ❌ No |
| Random Forest | ❌ No |
| XGBoost | ❌ No |

